+## Modes & deterministic runner (2026-07-06 Phase-1 upgrade — additive)
+
+The deterministic half of this review now lives in a runner; call it instead
+of re-deriving numbers by hand (DR-004 computed-not-claimed):
+
+```bash
+python <path-to-your-clone>/scripts/run_ai_review.py --mode <mode> [--dry-run]
+```
+
+Modes → tier mapping (each mode's judgment checklist:
+`fable-style-project-harness/prompts/ai-review-modes.md`):
+
+| Tier | Runner modes to fold in |
+|---|---|
+| weekly | `standard_review` + `diff_review --since-ref <last-review-tag>` |
+| monthly | weekly + `harness_cleanup_review` + `code_invocation_review` |
+| quarterly | monthly + `codex_delegation_review` + `experiment_review` |
+
+Flow: run the mode → read `reports/ai-review/latest.json` (gitignored, local)
+→ answer the mode's semantic checklist with cited evidence → write findings
+JSON per `schemas/recommendation.schema.yaml` → re-run with
+`--ingest findings.json`. The runner renders JSON→Markdown deterministically
+and appends `reports/ai-review/history/review-log.jsonl` — do NOT hand-write
+report numbers; embed the runner's output in the audits/*.md report.
+
+Codex delegation checks in this review follow the canonical policy:
+`fable-style-project-harness/docs/codex-delegation-policy.md` (one tripwire
+number: ≥3 files; supersedes any "≥5 files" statement elsewhere).
+
+Scheduled use: `--mode scheduled_review` is report-only BY DESIGN
+(source=scheduled_runner; deterministic scans; no ledger writes, no
+proposals, no application — doctrine-compatible with "the consumer is a
+present human"). The existing ClaudeAiReviewDue nudge task stays the
+summoner; if you also want a machine report waiting for you, register:
+`schtasks /create /tn ClaudeAiReviewScheduledScan /sc weekly /d MON /st 09:05 /tr "python <path-to-your-clone>/scripts/run_ai_review.py --mode scheduled_review"`
+(human decision — never auto-registered).
